-- Italy, Paraguay Tied 0-0 in First Half of World Cup Group F Game
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-14T18:45:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/italy-paraguay-tied-0-0-in-first-half-of-world-cup-group-f-game.html

          
          
             Defending champion Italy was tied 0-
0 against Paraguay after 15 minutes of their opening Group F
match at soccer’s World Cup in Cape Town, South Africa.   
 Italy, which has progressed from the group stage at the
past eight World Cups, is aiming to match Brazil’s record five
titles.  
 New Zealand and Slovakia are also in Group F.  
          
          


  


        